  "summary": "安阳警方悬赏10万元捉拿公交持刀杀人的周姓嫌疑人（黄县人，1989年5月生）。该嫌疑人于周一下午在安阳至北郭乡的公交上行凶，当时一身酒气，造成3人死亡（含10个月女婴、10岁男童、17岁男青年）、12人受伤（5人重伤，含刚获大学录取通知书的18岁少女）。嫌疑人被抓时仍穿行凶时的血衣，警方已通过指纹和DNA确认其身份。"
}

{
  "summary": "Nottinghamshire Police received a report of a large gathering in a marquee at a Bestwood, Nottingham property around 20:30 BST on Friday. The organiser was issued a large fine, as the gathering violated England's current socialising guidelines which permit a maximum of two households or six people to socialise in parks and private gardens. Assistant Chief Constable Gerard Milano noted that while the force does not wish to disrupt people's fun, it must take action against clear, deliberate breaches of regulations, and will continue to follow the engage-explain-encourage-act approach aligned with the government's roadmap. The text also invites readers to follow BBC East Midlands on social media and submit story ideas to their email address, with a related link to Nottinghamshire Police."
}

{
  "summary": "Two foxes have died in Kidbrooke, Greenwich, after being shot with arrows—one was taken to a Kent charity for treatment but passed away, while another was found dead earlier. A third fox was also spotted with an arrow in its body. The Met Police's Wildlife Crime Unit described these deliberate killings as disturbing and shocking. The Fox Project charity is offering a £2,000 reward for information leading to a conviction, as using bows or crossbows to kill wild animals is illegal. The charity's founder, whose rescue centre treats over 1,000 foxes annually, called the case extremely shocking and expressed dismay at the small minority of people capable of such extreme animal cruelty."
}

{
  "summary": "37-year-old Baljit Singh's body was discovered by emergency services in a Hayes alleyway off Station Road at 22:56 BST on Saturday. A post-mortem examination confirmed his death was caused by neck compression, with police suspecting he was assaulted following an argument. No arrests have been made yet, and the Met Police are seeking to trace two men who were with Singh shortly before his death. Det Ch Insp Helen Rance described the attack as a vicious fatal assault; officers are reviewing hours of CCTV footage and interviewing local residents to identify those responsible. Police are appealing for anyone present in the Station Road area from 22:00 onward that Saturday to come forward. Additionally, people can follow London news via Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, and the associated YouTube channel."
}

{
  "summary": "Nigel Pope filmed a four-part series documenting a year in the Inner and Outer Hebrides. VisitScotland hopes the series will boost tourism in the region, following the success of prior programs like Island Parish (which saw a 10% footfall rise at Barra's VisitScotland Information Centre) and Balamory (linked to a 15.5% increase in Calmac passenger numbers during its peak popularity). VisitScotland chairman Mike Cantlay noted the series is a golden opportunity to promote the Year of Natural Scotland, as it will highlight Scotland's landscapes, wildlife, and people positively; research shows one in five visitors are influenced by on-screen depictions of Scotland, making such exposure highly beneficial for tourism."
